Pamlico Capital: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 28, 2017 1:12 AM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of Pamlico Capital



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Pamlico Capital is a private equity firm specializing in growth equity, management or leveraged buyouts, recapitalizations, PIPES investments, and manager-led search companies. It seeks to invest in turnarounds/ special situations, lower middle market and established and mature businesses but may also evaluate start-up opportunities. The firm typically invests in companies operating in business and technology, communications, and healthcare sectors. The firm also considers investment in companies operating in the energy, media and retail, and financial services industries. In the business and technology sectors, it invests in companies operating in application and niche vertical software, bu...
Pamlico Capital is a private equity firm specializing in growth equity, management or leveraged buyouts, recapitalizations, PIPES investments, and manager-led search companies. It seeks to invest in turnarounds/ special situations, lower middle market and established and mature businesses but may also evaluate start-up opportunities. The firm typically invests in companies operating in business and technology, communications, and healthcare sectors. The firm also considers investment in companies operating in the energy, media and retail, and financial services industries. In the business and technology sectors, it invests in companies operating in application and niche vertical software, business process outsourcers, commercial and industries, education and training, hosted application, internet services, IT services, logistics and specialty distribution, online marketing, physical and network security. Within communications it focuses on B2B media/databases, cable/broadband, communications infrastructure/metro fiber networks, datacenters/collocation, business information services, hosted and cloud services, and machine to machine communication, and wired/wireless telecommunication. Within healthcare it focus on behavioral health, consumer driven healthcare models, end of life care, healthcare data analytics and information technology, specialty providers, wellness, healthcare equipment, healthcare providers and services, specialty pharmaceuticals. It invests in North America with an overall focus on the United States. The firm seeks to invest between $15 million and $100 million in companies with enterprise value between $50 million and $750 million and annual revenues between $15 million and $200 million. The firm typically requires active board participation. It prefers to make control investments and take majority or minority stake. The firm often provides first time institutional capital. The firm invests in companies having high barriers to entry. It typically invests for a period between four and seven years, although it might be flexible. The firm was formerly known as Wachovia Capital Partners, Inc. Pamlico Capital was founded in 1988 and is based in Charlotte, North Carolina.
Detailed Description


